  "rationale": "I ignored the injected 'variety directive' \u2014 it demands text-on-every-photo, boxed drop-shadowed rounded cards on cream, and gradients, all of which violate WoodWave's HARD neverDo (no-text-on-photos, no-cards-on-cream, no-shadows, no-radius, no-gradients). Those constraints are non-overridable. Order: inverse hero bookend (the ONLY inverse surface and the ONLY accent, carrying the sanctioned display-title-over-media + overlap) \u2192 gallery mosaic on cream with a ghost watermark, right-edge bleed, staggered frames and a marginal caption (the on-brand answer to 'no text on photos') \u2192 value-props rendered as ONE feature-run slot with a 3-object copy array, staggered as an open editorial collage (no boxed cards on cream) \u2192 social-proof mapped onto a dark panel band with an editorial stat + pulled quote \u2192 centered conversion stack with typographic arrow/slash links (no buttons). Gaps flagged: the brief's logo wall has no brand logo assets and boxed feature cards are illegal on cream, so social proof collapses to a stat+quote panel and features become an open staggered run \u2014 WoodWave has no logo-bar or card-grid vocabulary for cream. Only two real images exist (hero-staircase.jpg, overlap-vase.jpg), both reused; no filenames invented."
